{"author":{"id":"1260ec7e1e5fa2a41651bb0f92ca6302285a1546d07f404ff26b865b47ab5c24"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1637013231,"nonce":"r09fneVT/bYlgv6dHLrCcCq9AQY=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc45xzZu","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/835#issuecomment-969356910"},"message":"\u003e I'm trying to consider users who are not comfortable with the terminal at all and want an entirely terminal-free installation and usage.\n\nfor those an ideal one would be an entirely web UI for upload at dandiarchive.org but I bet we would quickly run into troubles given the sizes of our datasets.  With a nuitka build of dandi client I think it would be feasible to wrap it into some \"installer\" so people could just download + install, and that would create the \"DANDI app\" \"icon\" to click on, so ppl could get to it without seeing a command line.  Do you know any other App which uses libhdf5 and has some nice GUI with cross-platform installer?","files":null}]}